A 25-year-old motorcyclist was struck and killed on the Brooklyn-Queens Expressway by a hit-and-run driver, police said. The motorcyclist was traveling eastbound on the Williamsburg Bridge ramp, entering the BQE at 4:15 a.m. Saturday when he was hit by another vehicle, “possibly a taxi” that kept on going, the NYPD said. The victim was severely injured and pronounced dead at the scene, police said. His name was not yet released. There were no arrests. The NYPD’s Highway Collision Investigation Squad is investigating.